{{Infobox writer <!-- For more information see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]]. --> | name = | image = Thomas van Aalten (2016).jpg | caption = Thomas van Aalten (2016) | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1978, September 26 | birth_place = Huissen, Gelderland | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|Year|Month|Day|Year|Month|Day}} --> | death_place = | resting_place = | occupation = Writer | language = | nationality = Dutch | ethnicity = | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = | subject = | movement = | notableworks = | spouse = | partner = | children = | relatives = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | website = | portaldisp = }} '''Thomas van Aalten''' (born September 26, 1978 in [[Huissen]], [[Gelderland]]) is a [[Dutch people|Dutch]] writer. He made his debut with a story in the [[literature|literary]] magazine ''Zoetermeer'', at the age of 19. Van Aalten has written the novels ''Sneeuwbeeld'' (2000),<ref>{{cite news |title=Likkende vlammen, rottende schedels, instortende nieuwbouw |url=http://www.trouw.nl/krantenarchief/2000/04/08/2437513/Likkende_vlammen__rottende_schedels__instortende_nieuwbouw.html |work=[[Trouw]] |date=8 April 2000 |accessdate=24 December 2009 }}</ref> ''Tupelo'' (2001),<ref>{{cite news |title=De vervreemding is volledig |url=http://www.recensieweb.nl/recensie/1796/De+vervreemding+is+volledig.html |work=Recensieweb |date=17 May 2006 |accessdate=24 December 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727075004/http://www.recensieweb.nl/recensie/1796/De+vervreemding+is+volledig.html |archivedate=27 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> ''Sluit Deuren en Ramen'' (2003),<ref>{{cite news |title=Boeken fictie |url=http://www.trouw.nl/krantenarchief/2003/05/24/2183993/BOEKEN_FICTIE.html |work=[[Trouw]] |date=24 May 2003 |accessdate=24 December 2009 }}</ref> ''Coyote'' (2006) and ''De Onderbreking'' (2009)<ref>{{cite news |title=De Onderbreking |url=http://llink.nl/obalive/viewpage.php?page=toonuitzending&datum=2009-01-19 |work=[[LLiNK]] |date=19 January 2009 |accessdate=24 December 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120710114629/http://llink.nl/obalive/viewpage.php?page=toonuitzending&datum=2009-01-19 |archivedate=10 July 2012 |df= }}</ref> and several articles for magazines such as [[3VOOR12]], [[Passionate]], VARA TV Magazine, Revu and [[Vrij Nederland]]. Van Aalten's style is characterized by absurd dialogues, creepy atmospheres and strange characters. He is a [[F.C. St. Pauli]] enthusiast and fan of rock music like [[Motörhead]], [[The Sisters of Mercy]]. Van Aalten also often works together with Berlin-based burlesque filmmaker [[Edwin Brienen]].
His 'fifth novel' was a stunt; ''Exile'' appeared only on a mobile phone after sending an SMS text message.<ref>{{cite news |title=Roman alleen op mobieltje |url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/multimedia/article405362.ece/Roman_alleen_op_mobieltje |work=[[De Volkskrant]] |date=12 March 2007 |accessdate=24 December 2009 }}</ref> The story contained comments on the abuse of new technologies.
