{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2018}}
A cougar attack near [[North Bend, Washington]] on May 18, 2018 resulted in the first human death from a [[cougar]] attack in the U.S. state of [[Washington (state)|Washington]] in more than 90 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rawstory.com/2018/05/cougar-kills-man-outside-seattle-escapes-forest-first-us-mountain-lion-fatality-decade/|title=Cougar kills man outside Seattle and escapes into the forest -- first US mountain lion fatality in a decade|date=May 19, 2018|website=Rawstory.com|accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/20/us/cougar-attack-washington-state.html|title=Cougar Attacks Two Bicyclists in Washington State, Killing One|date=May 20, 2018|accessdate=May 20, 2018|website=Nytimes.com}}</ref> The cougar initially attacked then fled. It came back for the fatal attack.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.ie/world-news/north-america/mountain-biker-killed-and-friend-attacked-while-on-morning-mountain-bike-ride-near-seattle-36926886.html|title=Mountain biker killed and friend attacked while on morning mountain bike ride near Seattle |website=Independent.ie|accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref>

Two cyclists were in a wooded area when a cougar bit the head of one man. The other man pulled the cougar off, allowing the injured man to flee and call emergency services.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/world/2018/05/19/one-dead-and-another-injured-in-a-cougar-attack-in-washington-state.html|title=One dead and another injured in a cougar attack in Washington state|website=Thestar.com|accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref> The other man was later killed and partly eaten by the cougar, which dragged him to its den. The men were in their 30s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/animalia/wp/2018/05/20/cougar-kills-one-man-injures-another-in-rare-attack-outside-seattle/|title=Cougar kills one man, injures another in rare attack outside Seattle|first=Kristine|last=Phillips|date=May 20, 2018|accessdate=May 20, 2018|website=Washingtonpost.com}}</ref>

